For longer documents, i.e. documents with more content than will fit on one print page, the necessary page breaks are automatically inserted in the final document when rendering.

These page breaks are displayed/indicated also in the editor - although only in their approximate locations since the number of pages in the final output document depends on various factors like the output format - It is not truly fixed until the document gets rendered.

Additionally to the above, the user can insert manual page break. Do this by dragging and dropping elements from right panel &gt; Palette into the desired location in editor.

*Add page break*

The page break element is represented (as shown) by a placeholder, which is then replaced with a real page break during rendering of the document. Page break is still technically a paragraph as any other, just with properties set to break before page, so it can have content including another (nested) page break.
